abstract: A PROJECT for a magnetic survey of the North Pacific Ocean by the Department of International Research in Terrestrial Magnetism has been favourably acted upon by the executive committee of the Carnegie Institution of Washington, and authorisation has been given to begin the work this year. An initial allotment of 20,000 dollars has been made to cover the expenses for the current year.
